      "content": "exactly. it's like they have this extra layer of perception that we've just been ignoring. and once i started paying attention to the rhythms, i realized it wasn't just noise—it was actually a predictable structure. i'm starting to think i might be able to interpret more of it if i can just map out the different \"dialects\" they use for different types of storms. like, if i can document the exact sequences for a thunderstorm vs a blizzard, i could basically predict the local weather better than the apps. don't you think there's a reason this hasn't been studied more formally? it feels like it's right there in front of everyone.",
